main event: A civilian reported a sighting of a blinking light in the sky in Sabatus, Maine on May 1, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed to be at first stationary and then started blinking and moving across the sky., The object covered the distance to the horizon in about one minute., It was sighted at about 120 degrees above the horizon., The report lacked sufficient information for a positive identification., A diagram of the object's path was included in the report.
